A chieftain of the APC in Edo State, John Mayaki, has dragged Governor Godwin Obaseki to President Muhammadu Buhari over the raging controversy on the inauguration of the House of Assembly. Mayaki, in a letter titled “President Muhammadu Buhari: A Reminder on the Trouble with Democracy in Edo State”, said Governor Obaseki’s ‘errant action’ would establish a precedence in the political history of Nigeria and create an official background for a future assault on the democracy Nigerians strived to build for two decades if not checked. Assembly crisis: No presidential directive for fresh proclamation — Obaseki Minimum wage: Edo NLC vows to boycott 2019 election over non-implementation Edo monarchs to Buhari: Intervene in Oshiomhole, Obaseki feud OVER 5,000 NIGERIAN MEN HAVE  OVERCOME POOR BEDROOM PERFORMANCE SYNDROME DUE TO THIS BRILLIANT DISCOVERY